[00:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'talk about what makes this special. &gt;&gt; Thank you. Super excited to finally be able to talk about this. Spent 10 years in development in the drive and we finally get to show it off today. ICAS 2025. What we\'re showing today is the'

[00:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'FluxJet kayak, the world\'s first fully integrated electric jet propelled kayak. What that means is that you get a kayak that just looks like a kayak, but also has the benefits of having a drone. It has zero draft, zero hassles. It comes'

[01:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'ready to run. You drop the battery in, you\'re off. &gt;&gt; So, let\'s start off kind of maybe bow and go to stern. And you can just kind of talk about why you designed it the'

[01:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'way you designed it here. &gt;&gt; Yeah. With the boat, what you\'re going to see is this front section is flex space. So, in the rigged out boat, you\'ll see we got the cover on, &gt;&gt; but you could also open it up like that boat and have a totally open deck.'

[01:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; We really wanted to give you maximum deck space that you can use however you want to use it. So, this cover is removable, so you can pop this guy off. Right now, we\'ve got a little cooler. We got our Buffalo Gear cooler under there. Super sweet. Keep your drinks. But you'

[01:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'can also pull this out and use this for different components. So, one of the really cool ones that we\'re excited about is the kids jump seat. So, you\'ll be able to actually pull this off and we\'ve got a little stadium seat that Bungie\'s in. So, you can have your kids'

[01:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'sit up in the front. Coming over here, it looks like we got some graphs also. So, yeah, on a rigged out boat, we went hard. Garmin hooked us up with a pair of Ultra 2 106 SV 10-in graphs, and they are absolutely amazing. And that paired'

[02:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'perfectly with the Sidescan sonar transducer which is hidden in a pocket up inside the bottom of our boat. So there\'s absolutely nothing hanging over. &gt;&gt; Now for that transducer, do the wires go'

[02:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'down through the here? &gt;&gt; Yep. You pop them right down through the scupper down to the transducer port there. &gt;&gt; Yeah. &gt;&gt; As we move back and see we\'ve got our control panel here.'

[02:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'We got battery right here under the seat. We got our main power breaker that shuts everything off. It comes back around. And one of the things people really excited about is our voltage regulators. So the boat internally can take any voltage from 12 to 60 volts. So'

[02:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'you can drop any standard group up to group 31 battery you want in there. And the boat will automatically give you 5 amps at 5 volts and 10 amps at 12 volts off of one battery. So all of our graphs right now are running off this 36V'

[03:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'battery without having to have any other stuff. It\'s just ready to So, it\'s automatically switching voltage based on what the draw is and and what\'s connected. &gt;&gt; Yeah. So, we\'ve got an output right'

[03:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'here. There\'s an IP67 5V out for your phone charger, GoPro charge, and that kind of stuff. You\'ve got two buttons here. One controls our deck lights, one\'s for our navigation lights. They\'re also included. And then there will be an'

[03:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'output, a 12volt output. Most likely, we\'re going to put it right here. And that\'ll be able to power your fish finders and that sort of stuff. So you can run this on a 12vt battery &gt;&gt; all the way up to a 60 volt.'

[03:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; Yeah. Your power is going to scale with your battery voltage. So basically if you drop a 12vt in there, you\'re only going to get trolling mower power. You\'re going to be 3 m an hour somewhere around there, right? You\'re going to get that 30 lb of thrust. As you step it up to 36, you\'re going to get that full 6 7'

[03:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'mph, the full power of it. And then it will stay about that same power all the way to 60 volts. So it basically caps out once you give it 36. &gt;&gt; That is super cool. And it also solves'

[04:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'the noise problem. So people, &gt;&gt; right, &gt;&gt; experts we\'ve been talking to are saying that they have noise issues in their in their sonar systems. And because that voltage regulator is stepping down voltage, it filters out all that noise'

[04:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'for you. So you don\'t have to worry about that. &gt;&gt; Okay. Now, how are where where is the jet drive? I mean, so I see the batteries in here, but we got it. It\'s &gt;&gt; Yeah. So the jet drive'

[04:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; Oh, it\'s like it\'s like a jet ski kayak. &gt;&gt; Yeah, sort of. &gt;&gt; Yeah. It has an intake and then you got your a cone there. &gt;&gt; So the big difference is that with a jet ski, they\'re designed for maximum performance and they and because of that they scoop up water and in doing so they'

[04:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'scoop up everything. So with this drive, what we did was optimize it for maximum straining. So this pump is designed to only take in water and it took us a year of CFD design to get that thing just'

[04:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'right to where it will float clean over grass and not pick anything up. But it is amazing. Combine that with a super shallow draft and you float right over the weeds without even disturbing them. &gt;&gt; Wow, that is super cool. So, your foot'

[05:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'steering comes back to this turntable. Works just like a typical rudder. And that articulates your nozzle down below. So, you can see that nozzle is how you steer without the need for a rudder. &gt;&gt; Oh, really? We designed it so you also'

[05:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'can if you\'re doing big open water and you want more tracking, we have inserts and then there\'s two mounts here. So you can actually attach your rudder to this plate and it will actually turn your rudder in conjunction with the nozzle if'

[05:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'you want that too. So &gt;&gt; okay, giving you maximum options. So &gt;&gt; one of the neat things too, our 360 pole light is over in the new product showcase, but we also have a power output here that powers your 360.'

[05:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; I saw that. Yeah. Yeah. Really cool. &gt;&gt; Yeah. All integrated. I got four rod holders, two forward, two rear. &gt;&gt; This is your your throttle then. &gt;&gt; This is your throttle. So, one of our design ethos is we want this thing to be super simple. An iPhone does not come'

[05:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'with an instruction manual. We want this thing to be FisherPrice easy. And we don\'t want you to have to look for the throttle. I don\'t want anything my line is going to catch on, right? I just want the throttle where I can reach down. I put my thumb on there and I go forward.'

[06:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'I go backward. It\'s that easy. &gt;&gt; Rock it back and forth. &gt;&gt; That\'s it. And it\'s got a nice detent in the center so you know where stop is. just make it super clean. There\'s nothing to take on, nothing to put off. And then there is a matching part on the other side. If you want to flip it over'

[06:25] [scene:talk]
